==English==
===Etymology===
Via Middle English and Old French from Latin ''[[mantellum]]''
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun-reg}}

# a piece of [[clothing]] somewhat like an open [[robe]] or [[cloak]], especially that worn by [[Orthodox]] [[bishop]]s
#(''figurative'') anything that [[cover]]s or [[conceal]]s something else
# the [[zone]] of hot [[gas]]es around a [[flame]]; the [[gauzy]] [[incandescent]] [[covering]] of a [[gas lamp]]
#{{anatomy}} the [[cerebral cortex]]
#{{geology}} the [[layer]] between the [[Earth]]'s [[core]] and [[crust]]
#{{zoology}} the [[body]] [[wall]] of a [[mollusc]]/[[mollusk]]
#An alternative spelling '''[[mantel]]'''
{{wikipediapar|mantle (geology)}}
{{wikipediapar|mantle (mollusc)}}

